description:
## Problem

Current Buck2 configuration uses flat option names with language prefixes:

```nix
buck2.goDepsFile
buck2.goModFile
buck2.goSumFile
buck2.rustDepsFile
buck2.rustFeaturesFile
buck2.cargoTomlFile
buck2.cargoLockFile
buck2.pythonDepsFile
buck2.pyprojectFile
buck2.pylockFile
buck2.rustcFlagsRegistry
buck2.buildScriptFixups
```

This becomes unwieldy as we add more languages and options.

## Proposed Solution

Refactor to language-specific namespaces with per-language enable flags:

```nix
buck2.go = {
  enable = true;  # Enable Go toolchain support
  depsFile = ./go-deps.toml;
  modFile = "go.mod";
  sumFile = "go.sum";
};

buck2.rust = {
  enable = true;  # Enable Rust toolchain support
  depsFile = ./rust-deps.toml;
  featuresFile = ./rust-features.toml;
  cargoTomlFile = "Cargo.toml";
  cargoLockFile = "Cargo.lock";
  rustcFlagsRegistry = { ... };
  buildScriptFixups = { ... };
};

buck2.python = {
  enable = true;  # Enable Python toolchain support
  depsFile = ./python-deps.toml;
  pyprojectFile = "pyproject.toml";
  lockFile = "pylock.toml";
};
```

The `enable` flag per language:
- Controls whether the language cell is generated
- Controls whether sync rules are added for that language
- Allows selective enablement (e.g., Rust-only project)
- Defaults could be auto-detected from file presence

## Benefits

- Clearer organization by language
- Per-language enable/disable without removing all config
- Easier to add new language-specific options
- Better discoverability (tab completion shows all go.* options)
- Consistent naming within each namespace (depsFile vs goDepsFile/rustDepsFile/pythonDepsFile)

## Files to Update

1. `nix/flake-parts/turnkey/default.nix` - option definitions
2. `nix/devenv/turnkey/buck2.nix` - option consumers
3. `flake.nix` (turnkey repo) - update example usage
4. Documentation

## Migration

Consider keeping old flat names as deprecated aliases for backwards compatibility, or do a clean break since this is pre-1.0.
